        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
        <h3>What does a financial consultant do?</h3>
        <p>Financial consultants analyze financial data, create budgets, advise on investments, and provide strategic guidance to improve decision-making and growth.</p>

        <h3>How is a financial consultant different from an accountant?</h3>
        <p>Unlike accountants who focus on bookkeeping and compliance, financial consultants provide strategic insights, forecasts, and actionable recommendations.</p>

        <h3>How do I become a financial consultant?</h3>
        <p>By earning relevant education, gaining professional experience, developing analytical skills, and establishing credibility through publications or news coverage.</p>

        <h3>Why is financial consulting important for businesses?</h3>
        <p>It ensures efficient resource allocation, risk management, and informed decision-making, enabling sustainable growth and profitability.</p>

